MAN PAGE 


.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 2022 - 12 - 9 Linux "USER MANUALS"

.SH NAME

Simple Shell - Simple Unix command language interpreter

.SH SYPNOSIS
.TP
.B interactive format
"./hsh"
.TP
.B non-interactive format
"echo /bin/ls | ./hsh"

.SH DESCRIPTION

Simple shell is a command language interpreter written by Ken Thompson. It is designed to execute commands, and readfrom the standard input. The shell is a command line interface (CLI) program that takes commands from the keyboard and gives them to the operating system to perform. 

.SS PATH
It does not yet handle piping, redirections, pattern matching, variables expansions.

.SH BUILTINS

.The following built in commands are supported:

.IT

.B env

- prints the environment variables

.B exit

- exits the program

.B /bin/ls

- prints a list of files in the current directory


.SS Command Execution
After a command has been split into words, if it results in a simple command and an optional list of arguments, the following actions are taken.

/bin/ls

.IP [[flags]...[arguments]]
Lists files in the current directory according to the flags given by user

